OL,3,CPeople smuggler who 'managed' #12m
OL,4,Cboat crossings jailed for 25 years
OL,6,FHe was living on benefits in a
OL,7,Ftaxpayer-funded home, having arrived
OL,8,Fin the country as an asylum seeker in
OL,9,F2022, according to reports, despite a
OL,10,Fprevious drug-smuggling conviction in
OL,11,FItaly.
OL,13,FThe defendant, who is believed to be
OL,14,Fthe first person convicted of
OL,15,Forganising boat crossings across the
OL,16,FMediterranean from the UK, was
OL,17,Fsentenced at Southwark Crown Court on
OL,18,FTuesday to 25 years, having pleaded
OL,19,Fguilty to conspiracy to assist
OL,20,Funlawful immigration.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/17
