OL,6,FHe added: "There has to be, it seems
OL,7,Fto me, a crystal-clear message
OL,8,Fdelivered to those engaged in this
OL,9,Ftrade, that the protection of
OL,10,Finternational borders is also
OL,11,Fsomething that, when the court has
OL,12,Fsuch a responsibility, is taken very
OL,13,Fseriously indeed and reflected in a
OL,14,Flengthy sentence being passed."
OL,16,FThe defendant was heard ranting in the
OL,17,Fdock after the sentencing, while a
OL,18,Fwoman in the public gallery wept.
